  "texts": [
    "This leaves two difficult paths forward: either demonstrate generalization empirically by testing across significantly broader domain samples, or explicitly map which specific domains exhibit desirable safety properties and which do not.",
    "Either way forward requires comprehensive testing across deployment contexts, moving away from assumptions about principled behavior toward empirical characterization of context-dependent patterns.",
    "Safety Properties Fail to Generalize Across ContextsA growing body of evidence demonstrates that safety and alignment properties in language models fail to generalize across contexts in ways that undermine deployment reliability.",
    "Recent work shows that safety training focused on natural language inputs fails to transfer to code domains, with transformed prompts bypassing guardrails over 80% of the time [32].",
    "Similarly, models struggle to apply established safety facts across domains, with top performers achieving only 58% accuracy despite weak correlation between model capabilities and performance [5]."
  ],
